  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows two scenarios of a circular loop with variable radius. In Scenario 1, the loop begins with radius R, and after a time delta t it has radius 2 R. In Scenario 2, the loop begins with radius R, and after a time delta t it has radius one half R.\" src=\"/images/c2a5a3d46027da3d970b92d9c5047504.svg\"></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A loop with variable radius is in a constant magnetic field. The field is directed perpendicular to the plane of the loop. In Scenario <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"e m f\"><math alttext=\"e m f\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>emf</mi></math></span></span> <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the absolute value of open E sub 1\"><math alttext=\"the absolute value of open E sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mpadded><mo>|</mo><mpadded><msub><mi>Ɛ</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mpadded><mo>|</mo></mpadded></math></span></span> is induced when the radius of the loop increases from <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R\"><math alttext=\"R\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>R</mi></math></span></span> to <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 R\"><math alttext=\"2 R\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi></math></span></span> during time <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"delta t\"><math alttext=\"delta t\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi><mi>t</mi></math></span></span>. In Scenario <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"e m f\"><math alttext=\"e m f\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>emf</mi></math></span></span> <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the absolute value of open E sub 2\"><math alttext=\"the absolute value of open E sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mpadded><mo>|</mo><mpadded><msub><mi>Ɛ</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mpadded><mo>|</mo></mpadded></math></span></span> is induced when the radius of the loop decreases from <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R\"><math alttext=\"R\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>R</mi></math></span></span> to <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R over 2\"><math alttext=\"R over 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mi>R</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></span></span> in the same amount of time <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"delta t\"><math alttext=\"delta t\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi><mi>t</mi></math></span></span>. Which of the following correctly compares <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the absolute value of open E sub 1\"><math alttext=\"the absolute value of open E sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mpadded><mo>|</mo><mpadded><msub><mi>Ɛ</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mpadded><mo>|</mo></mpadded></math></span></span> to <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the absolute value of open E sub 2\"><math alttext=\"the absolute value of open E sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mpadded><mo>|</mo><mpadded><msub><mi>Ɛ</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mpadded><mo>|</mo></mpadded></math></span></span>?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i1",
